cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SP 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the statistics of the Nonlinear Fourier Transform (NFT) of a pulse in the presence of additive Gaussian noise. Information theory is concerned with the quantification, storage, and communication of information, and the NFT is a tool for signal processing and communication. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a novel approach to compute the whole discrete spectrum of a pulse using the Fourier Collocation (FC) method, which is a numerical method. 
- cs.SI (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the analysis of the statistics of the NFT of a pulse, which can be seen as a system or a control problem. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new algorithm (FC method) to compute the NFT of a pulse, which can be seen as a data structure or an algorithmic problem. 
- cs.SP (Signal Processing): The NFT is a tool for signal processing, and the paper deals with the statistics of the NFT of a pulse in the presence of noise.
